metadata.name: Brahma
metadata.description:
Brahma is a god who created the world and everything in the world. He is one of the trinity gods of Hinduism, the other two being Shiva and Vishnu. Brahma is the creator, Vishnu is the sustainer and Shiva is the destroyer. However, Brahma is regarded as the most senior of the gods.  
Brahma is considered the father of dharma, which means "righteousness."
